      <p class="deets">
        I hope I've provided some understanding for how complicated an issue teaching
        English in elementary school is and how much effort it takes from ALTs,
        teachers and the Board of Education to make the most of limited classtime and
        resources and help students get the most out of all that effort.
      </p>
      <p>
        I haven't even touched on many other challenges...
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The language barrier between teachers and ALTs.
        </li>
        <li>
          Differences in, not only culture but personality.
        </li>
        <li>
          Students with special needs, students who get themselves stuck in the
          "I don't speak English" category or students who are very very keen to
          learn English until in comes to speaking.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="deets">
        There is a lot I've left out but I've tried to be thorough. I've also tried to
        be more constructive than critical. Although, I've probably missed that mark a
        few times. I hope anyone who's come across this has gained at least
        some insight. I look forward to gaining further insight myself as time
        goes on. Thank you.
      </p>
